Improved motif __eq__ algorithm.
If the node degrees of these two motifs that are going to be compared
for equality differs from each other the __eq__ routine will return
False without starting to permute nodes. Better complexity.

Changed the folder structure of the project:

-classes		Where base classes are maintained
-family			Where class methods acting on objects of type family
            	are maintained.
--killer		Where killer functions that will be acting on ensembles
				that are family objects will be maintained.
-genetic 		Where class definitions and methods of GA are kept
-network 		Where mathods acting on elements of type network are kept.
--boolfuncs 	Where boolean functions that propoagte the state are housed
--motif 		Methods that extract motifs of a network are housed here.
--mutators 		Mutators that act upon networks are housed here
--scorers 		The functions that will return the score of an element of
				type network are kept here.
--selectors 	The functions that will decide whether an element of type
				network will be mutated and copied or not. 
-probes 		Functions and class definitions that are used in order to
				maintain the probe functionality.

Adding support for OpenMP
 - Changed setup script such that fopenmp lopenmp is passed as arguments
to the compiler.
 - added the boolfunction that advances a network multiple times as a C
extension.
 - The C extension uses openMP to divide the job into segments. Using
Python here introduces huge overhead.
 - Edited search_equilibrum and populate_equilibrium such that they can
call C type advance is needed.
 - Added the dynamic calibration of the amount of the orbit obtained by
the advance function at a single time. If the orbits are not found 1000
advances, the algorithm takes 1000 chunks of information rather than 1.
Trying to come up reasons why parallel is slower than serial.
